Preconditions:
The input `n` must be a positive integer.
The length of the arrays `leftChild` and `rightChild` must be equal to `n`.
The values in the arrays `leftChild` and `rightChild` must be within the range of `0` to `n - 1`.
The values in the arrays `leftChild` and `rightChild` must not have any duplicates.

Postconditions:
The method should return `true` if and only if all the given nodes form exactly one valid binary tree.
If the method returns `true`, it means that all the nodes form a valid binary tree.
If the method returns `false`, it means that the given nodes do not form a valid binary tree.